text: Obernzell () is a municipality in Passau in Bavaria in Germany. ==Geography== ===Geographical place=== Obernzell is in the Donau-Wald region at the Danube River. The middle of the Danube River makes the border with Upper Austria. ===Neighboring communities in Bavaria=== In Bavaria (Passau district): * Thyrnau * Untergriesbach In Upper Austria: * Vichtenstein * Esternberg ===Constituent communities=== The Obernzell Municipality has 21 Districts.: * Bärnbachmühle * Breitwies * Eckerstampf * Ederlsdorf * Edlhof * Erlau * Figermühle * Grub * Haar * Holzschleife * Hötzmannsöd * Leopoldsdorf * Matzenberg * Niedernhof * Nottau * Obernzell * Öd * Ödstadl * Rackling * Rollhäusl * Steinöd Hammermühle There are the districts of Ederlsdorf, Kellberg and Obernzell . ==History== ===Incorporations=== Once an independent municipality, Ederlsdorf was incorporated on July 1, 1972. ===Population development=== * 1970: 3.426 Residents * 1987: 3.425 Residents * 2000: 3.790 Residents * 2011: 3.850 Residents ==References== Category:Passau (district)
